headline.main: Moroccan Designer's Embroidery School Revives Fading Art
headline.print_headline: Moroccan Designer's Embroidery School Revives Fading Art

lead_paragraph: Chancellor Angela Merkel said on Friday Tunisia had agreed to take back 1,500 rejected Tunisian migrants from Germany, after an attack by a Tunisian on a Christmas market in Berlin which killed 12 people.
